headline: Nvidia's Gaming Business Could Be in Trouble
summary: Nvidia is prioritizing its data center business amid blockbuster AI chip demand.  The gaming business is suffering, evidenced by the company's buggy drivers.  Graphics processing unit (GPU) giant Nvidia (NASDAQ: NVDA) now generates most of its revenue from data center GPUs aimed at artificial intelligence (AI) workloads.
